Distribuciones

Num√©ricas

new_train1 %>% 
  select(Rating, which(sapply(., class) == "numeric")) %>% 
  select(-new_year) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = -Rating) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = value, fill = Rating, color = Rating)) +
  facet_wrap(~name, scales = "free", ncol = 3) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

Categ√≥ricas

  • Content_rating - Type:
new_train1 %>% 
  select_if(is.factor) %>% 
  select(-App) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = -Rating) %>%  
  filter(name %in% c("content_rating", "Type")) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = value, fill = Rating, color = Rating)) +
  facet_wrap(~name, scales = "free") +
  geom_bar(position = "fill", alpha = 0.5) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

  • Category - new_genres:
new_train1 %>% 
  select_if(is.factor) %>% 
  select(-App) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = -Rating) %>%  
  filter(name %in% c("Category", "new_genres")) %>%

Interacciones Dobles

  • Voy a explorar c√≥mo es el comportamiento (promedio) de las variables num√©ricas cuando son evaluadas en los niveles de la variable respuesta Rating y cada una de las variables categ√≥ricas.
  • Las interacciones dobles podr√≠an sugerir la necesidad de extraer nuevas caracter√≠sticas.

Rating-Content Rating

new_train1 %>% 
  select(Rating, content_rating, which(sapply(., class) == "numeric")) %>% 
  select(-new_year) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = !c(Rating, content_rating)) %>% 
  group_by(Rating, content_rating, name) %>% 
  summarise(promedio = mean(value, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = content_rating, y = promedio, color = Rating, group = Rating)) +
  facet_wrap(~name, scales = "free", ncol = 2) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  geom_line() +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

Rating-Type

new_train1 %>% 
  select(Rating, Type, which(sapply(., class) == "numeric")) %>% 
  select(-new_year) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = !c(Rating, Type)) %>% 
  group_by(Rating, Type, name) %>% 
  summarise(promedio = mean(value, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Type, y = promedio, color = Rating, group = Rating)) +
  facet_wrap(~name, scales = "free", ncol = 2) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  geom_line() +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

Rating-Category

new_train1 %>% 
  select(Rating, Category, which(sapply(., class) == "numeric")) %>% 
  select(-new_year) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = !c(Rating, Category)) %>% 
  group_by(Rating, Category, name) %>% 
  summarise(promedio = mean(value, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Category, y = promedio, color = Rating, group = Rating)) +
  facet_wrap(~name, scales = "free", ncol = 1) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  geom_line() +
  theme(legend.position = "top",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 35, hjust = 1))

ACP

library(tidymodels)
# "Receta" y "preparaci√≥n" para PCA y UMAP
receta_reductDim <- new_train1 %>%
  mutate(Rating = as.numeric(as.character(Rating))) %>% 
  select_if(is.numeric) %>% 
  select(-new_year) %>% 
  recipe(~ .) %>% 
  update_role(Rating, new_role = "id") %>% 
  step_knnimpute(all_predictors()) %>% 
  step_BoxCox(all_predictors()) %>%
  step_normalize(all_predictors()) %>% 
  step_pca(all_predictors())
  
pca_prep <- receta_reductDim %>% prep()
pca_prep
Data Recipe

Inputs:

Training data contained 5787 data points and 2083 incomplete rows. 

Operations:

K-nearest neighbor imputation for new_day, size_kb, new_installs, new_price, new_month_num, ... [trained]
Box-Cox transformation on new_day, size_kb, new_month_num, min_android, ... [trained]
Centering and scaling for Reviews, new_day, size_kb, new_installs, new_price, ... [trained]
PCA extraction with Reviews, new_day, size_kb, new_installs, new_price, ... [trained]
  • Recuperando resultados de PCA:
# Cargas (loadings)
tidy_pca <- tidy(pca_prep, 4) 
tidy_pca %>% 
  filter(component %in% paste0("PC", 1:5)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = value, y = terms, fill = value)) +
  facet_wrap(~component, ncol = 5) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE)

  • CP1 vs CP2:
juice(pca_prep) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = PC1, y = PC2, color = as.factor(Rating))) + 
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, lty = 2, lwd = 0.1) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, lty = 2, lwd = 0.1)

UMAP

library(embed)
# "Receta" y "preparaci√≥n"  UMAP
receta_umap <- new_train1 %>%
  mutate(Rating = as.numeric(as.character(Rating))) %>% 
  select_if(is.numeric) %>% 
  select(-new_year) %>% 
  recipe(~ .) %>% 
  update_role(Rating, new_role = "id") %>% 
  step_knnimpute(all_predictors()) %>% 
  step_BoxCox(all_predictors()) %>%
  step_normalize(all_predictors()) %>% 
  step_umap(all_predictors())
  
umap_prep <- receta_umap %>% prep()
umap_prep
Data Recipe

Inputs:

Training data contained 5787 data points and 2083 incomplete rows. 

Operations:

K-nearest neighbor imputation for new_day, size_kb, new_installs, new_price, new_month_num, ... [trained]
Box-Cox transformation on new_day, size_kb, new_month_num, min_android, ... [trained]
Centering and scaling for Reviews, new_day, size_kb, new_installs, new_price, ... [trained]
UMAP embedding for Reviews, new_day, size_kb, new_installs, new_price, ... [trained]
